{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882167633,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad353d8001XuK2FUKHP0KNzb","messageID":"msg_d7ad330500018776jvXIJe555O","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `cmd` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **agentd** — Idle cleanup controller binary that runs the Sandbox reconciler\n19: 2. **router** — HTTP session routing proxy with Gin framework\n20: 3. **workload-manager** — Sandbox orchestration controller with Kubernetes CRD management\n21: 4. **picod** — Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods\n22: \n23: These binaries serve as the deployment targets for the AgentCube platform, enabling independent scaling, deployment, and lifecycle management of each component.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scope\n28: \n29: ### In Scope\n30: \n31: | Item | Detail |\n32: |------|--------|\n33: | **Binary Entry Points** | 4 `main.go` files under `cmd/`: `agentd`, `router`, `workload-manager`, `picod` |\n34: | **Flag Parsing** | Standard Go `flag` package with `--help` support |\n35: | **Configuration** | CLI flags for service-specific settings (ports, timeouts, Kubernetes config) |\n36: | **Graceful Shutdown** | SIGINT/SIGTERM handling with configurable timeout |\n37: | **Dependency Wiring** | Initialize clients (Redis, Kubernetes, HTTP) from configuration |\n38: | **Service Startup** | Start controllers, HTTP servers, and reconcilers |\n39: | **Health Checks** | Basic liveness/readiness endpoints where applicable |\n40: | **Logging** | Structured startup logging with version and configuration |\n41: \n42: ### Out of Scope\n43: \n44: - Configuration file support (YAML/JSON config files)\n45: - Hot configuration reloading\n46: - Service discovery integration (Consul, etcd)\n47: - Metrics and monitoring endpoints (Prometheus)\n48: - Distributed tracing (Jaeger, Zipkin)\n49: - Circuit breaker patterns\n50: - Multi-instance leader election\n51: - Automated TLS certificate management\n52: - Plugin system for extensibility\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## Design\n57: \n58: ### File Structure\n59: \n60: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n61: |------|------|--------------|\n62: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Idle cleanup controller binary | ~80 |\n63: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Session routing proxy binary | ~100 |\n64: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Sandbox orchestration binary | ~120 |\n65: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Sandbox daemon binary | ~90 |\n66: \n67: ### Architecture\n68: \n69: ```\n70: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n71: │                        AgentCube Platform                            │\n72: │                                                                      │\n73: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n74: │  │   agentd     │  │    router    │  │workload-mgr  │  │  picod   │ │\n75: │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │ ┌──────┐ │ │\n76: │  │  │Reconciler│  │  │  │  Gin   │  │  │  │Controller│  │  │ │ HTTP │ │ │\n77: │  │  │(controller│  │  │  │Server  │  │  │  │ + API    │  │  │ │Server│ │ │\n78: │  │  │-runtime) │  │  │  │        │  │  │  │ Server   │  │  │ │      │ │ │\n79: │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │ └──┬───┘ │ │\n80: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │    │     │ │\n81: │  │  K8s API    │  │  Redis/Store │  │  K8s API      │  │ Workspace │ │\n82: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │    │     │ │\n83: │  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘  └───────┼──────┘  └────┼─────┘ │\n84: │          │                │                  │              │       │\n85: │          └────────────────┴──────────────────┴──────────────┘       │\n86: │                              │                                       │\n87: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n88: │                         + Redis/Valkey                              │\n89: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ### Binary Responsibilities\n93: \n94: #### agentd\n95: - Parse Kubernetes configuration flags\n96: - Initialize controller-runtime Manager with Sandbox scheme\n97: - Start idle cleanup reconciler\n98: - Handle graceful shutdown on signals\n99: \n100: #### router\n101: - Parse HTTP port and Redis connection flags\n102: - Initialize Gin HTTP server\n103: - Wire session routing middleware\n104: - Connect to workload manager backend\n105: - Handle graceful HTTP server shutdown\n106: \n107: #### workload-manager\n108: - Parse Kubernetes and Redis configuration\n109: - Initialize Sandbox controller (reconciler)\n110: - Start HTTP API server for sandbox management\n111: - Handle CRD lifecycle operations\n112: - Coordinate with optional Volcano scheduler\n113: \n114: #### picod\n115: - Parse HTTP port and workspace root flags\n116: - Initialize workspace directory\n117: - Start code execution HTTP handlers\n118: - Provide file upload/download endpoints\n119: - Support exec streaming for interactive sessions\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Execution Flows\n124: \n125: ### Common Binary Startup Flow\n126: \n127: ```\n128: main()\n129:     │\n130:     ▼\n131: ┌───────────────┐\n132: │ Parse Flags   │\n133: └───────┬───────┘\n134:         │\n135:         ▼\n136: ┌───────────────┐\n137: │ Validate      │\n138: │ Required Flags│\n139: └───────┬───────┘\n140:         │\n141:         ├─ Missing ──► Print Error + Exit(1)\n142:         │\n143:         ▼\n144: ┌───────────────┐\n145: │ Log Startup   │\n146: │ (version, cfg)│\n147: └───────┬───────┘\n148:         │\n149:         ▼\n150: ┌───────────────┐\n151: │ Initialize    │\n152: │ Dependencies  │\n153: └───────┬───────┘\n154:         │\n155:         ▼\n156: ┌───────────────┐\n157: │ Start Service │\n158: │ (blocking)    │\n159: └───────┬───────┘\n160:         │\n161:         ▼\n162: ┌───────────────┐\n163: │ Wait for      │\n164: │ SIGINT/SIGTERM│\n165: └───────┬───────┘\n166:         │\n167:         ▼\n168: ┌───────────────┐\n169: │ Graceful      │\n170: │ Shutdown      │\n171: └───────┬───────┘\n172:         │\n173:         ▼\n174:     Exit(0)\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### agentd Startup Flow\n178: \n179: ```\n180: main()\n181:     │\n182:     ▼\n183: Parse flags: --kubeconfig, --sync-period\n184:     │\n185:     ▼\n186: ctrl.GetConfigOrDie() // K8s config\n187:     │\n188:     ▼\n189: scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n190:     │\n191:     ▼\n192: Add Sandbox v1alpha1 to scheme\n193:     │\n194:     ▼\n195: ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.Options{\n196:     Scheme: scheme,\n197:     SyncPeriod: syncPeriod,\n198: })\n199:     │\n200:     ▼\n201: agentd.NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient())\n202:     │\n203:     ▼\n204: SetupWithManager(mgr)\n205:     │\n206:     ▼\n207: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### router Startup Flow\n211: \n212: ```\n213: main()\n214:     │\n215:     ▼\n216: Parse flags: --port, --redis-addr, --workload-manager\n217:     │\n218:     ▼\n219: Validate required flags\n220:     │\n221:     ▼\n222: redis.NewClient(redisAddr)\n223:     │\n224:     ▼\n225: store := router.NewSessionStore(redis)\n226:     │\n227:     ▼\n228: gin.New()\n229:     │\n230:     ▼\n231: router.SetupRoutes(engine, store, workloadMgrURL)\n232:     │\n233:     ▼\n234: http.ListenAndServe()\n235:     │\n236:     ▼\n237: Signal handling for graceful shutdown\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### workload-manager Startup Flow\n241: \n242: ```\n243: main()\n244:     │\n245:     ▼\n246: Parse flags: --port, --kubeconfig, --redis-addr, --default-image\n247:     │\n248:     ▼\n249: ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()\n250:     │\n251:     ▼\n252: scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n253: Add AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter to scheme\n254:     │\n255:     ▼\n256: ctrl.NewManager(...)\n257:     │\n258:     ▼\n259: workloadmanager.NewController(mgr, redis, config)\n260:     │\n261:     ▼\n262: Setup HTTP API server on --port\n263:     │\n264:     ▼\n265: Start both controller and HTTP server\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### picod Startup Flow\n269: \n270: ```\n271: main()\n272:     │\n273:     ▼\n274: Parse flags: --port, --workspace\n275:     │\n276:     ▼\n277: Resolve workspace to absolute path\n278: Create if not exists\n279:     │\n280:     ▼\n281: Validate workspace is writable\n282:     │\n283:     ▼\n284: http.NewServeMux()\n285:     │\n286:     ▼\n287: Register handlers:\n288:   - /execute (code execution)\n289:   - /upload (file upload)\n290:   - /download (file download)\n291:   - /exec (interactive exec)\n292:     │\n293:     ▼\n294: http.ListenAndServe()\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Interface\n300: \n301: ### agentd Flags\n302: \n303: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n304: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n305: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n306: | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Full sync period for all sandboxes |\n307: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n308: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n309: \n310: ### router Flags\n311: \n312: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n313: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n314: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n315: | `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug logging |\n316: | `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n317: | `--workload-manager` | string | (required) | Workload manager URL |\n318: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n319: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n320: \n321: ### workload-manager Flags\n322: \n323: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n324: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n325: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP API server port |\n326: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n327: | `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n328: | `--default-image` | string | \"ubuntu:22.04\" | Default sandbox image |\n329: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace |\n330: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n331: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n332: \n333: ### picod Flags\n334: \n335: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n336: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n337: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n338: | `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n339: | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n340: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Error Handling\n345: \n346: ### Error Types\n347: \n348: | Error | Description | Binary |\n349: |-------|-------------|--------|\n350: | `FlagError` | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n351: | `ConfigError` | Kubernetes config loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n352: | `ConnectionError` | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n353: | `SchemeError` | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n354: | `ServerError` | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n355: | `WorkspaceError` | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n356: \n357: ### Exit Codes\n358: \n359: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n360: |-----------|---------|\n361: | 0 | Clean shutdown |\n362: | 1 | Configuration error |\n363: | 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n364: | 3 | Server startup error |\n365: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n366: | 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ## Security Considerations\n371: \n372: ### RBAC Requirements\n373: \n374: #### agentd\n375: | Resource | Verbs |\n376: |----------|-------|\n377: | `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n378: \n379: #### router\n380: | Resource | Verbs |\n381: |----------|-------|\n382: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n383: \n384: #### workload-manager\n385: | Resource | Verbs |\n386: |----------|-------|\n387: | `agentruntimes` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n388: | `codeinterpreters` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n389: | `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n390: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n391: \n392: #### picod\n393: - Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n394: - Workspace directory isolation\n395: - No Kubernetes API access required\n396: \n397: ### Sensitive Data\n398: - Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n399: - Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n400: - No secrets logged at startup\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Impact Analysis\n405: \n406: ### Files Created\n407: \n408: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n409: |------|--------------|-------------|\n410: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~80 | Idle cleanup controller entry point |\n411: | `cmd/router/main.go` | ~100 | Session routing proxy entry point |\n412: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | ~120 | Sandbox orchestration entry point |\n413: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | ~90 | Sandbox daemon entry point |\n414: \n415: ### Dependencies\n416: \n417: ```go\n418: import (\n419:     \"flag\"\n420:     \"os\"\n421:     \"os/signal\"\n422:     \"syscall\"\n423:     \"time\"\n424:     \"context\"\n425:     \n426:     // Kubernetes\n427:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n428:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n429:     \n430:     // HTTP\n431:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n432:     \n433:     // Storage\n434:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n435:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n436:     \n437:     // AgentCube internal\n438:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n439:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n440:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n441:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n442:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n443: )\n444: ```\n445: \n446: | Package | Purpose |\n447: |---------|---------|\n448: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n449: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | K8s config loading |\n450: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for router |\n451: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n452: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n453: \n454: ### Downstream Consumers\n455: \n456: | Consumer | Usage |\n457: |----------|-------|\n458: | Helm Charts | Deploy binaries as container images |\n459: | Dockerfiles | Build container images for each binary |\n460: | CI/CD | Build and test binaries |\n461: | Local Development | Run services locally with `go run` |\n462: \n463: ### Performance Characteristics\n464: \n465: | Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n466: |--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n467: | agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n468: | router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n469: | workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n470: | picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Alternatives Considered\n475: \n476: ### Alternative 1: Single Binary with Subcommands\n477: \n478: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n479: |--------|------------|\n480: | **Pros** | Simpler deployment; single artifact; shared code |\n481: | **Cons** | Larger binary size; violates microservices pattern; harder to scale independently; all components must be updated together |\n482: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — AgentCube follows microservices architecture; independent scaling and deployment are requirements |\n483: \n484: ### Alternative 2: Configuration Files Instead of Flags\n485: \n486: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n487: |--------|------------|\n488: | **Pros** | More configuration options; easier to manage complex configs; version controlled |\n489: | **Cons** | Additional file management; less explicit; harder to debug; requires config reloading logic |\n490: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Flags are simpler for containerized environments (12-factor app); config files can be added later if needed |\n491: \n492: ### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n493: \n494: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n495: |--------|------------|\n496: | **Pros** | Cloud-native; works well with Kubernetes secrets; no command-line exposure |\n497: | **Cons** | Less discoverable; no built-in help; harder to validate at startup |\n498: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Flags provide better UX and discoverability; env vars can supplement flags for secrets |\n499: \n500: ### Alternative 4: Sidecar Pattern for picod\n501: \n502: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n503: |--------|------------|\n504: | **Pros** | Separation of concerns; independent updates |\n505: | **Cons** | More complex deployment; networking overhead; requires shared filesystem |\n506: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — picod is designed to run inside sandbox pods as the main process; sidecar adds unnecessary complexity |\n507: \n508: ---\n509: \n510: ## Risks and Mitigations\n511: \n512: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n513: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n514: | Flag parsing inconsistencies across binaries | Medium | Low | Use shared flag helper functions; consistent naming conventions |\n515: | Missing required flags in production | Medium | High | Fail fast with clear error messages; validate all required flags before startup |\n516: | Graceful shutdown timeout too short | Low | Medium | Configurable timeout with sensible default (30s); log warnings on timeout |\n517: | Kubernetes config loading failures | Medium | High | Support both in-cluster and external configs; clear error messages |\n518: | Redis connection failures at startup | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; fail fast after retries |\n519: | Binary size bloat from dependencies | Low | Medium | Use build flags `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`; multi-stage Docker builds |\n520: | Signal handling race conditions | Low | Medium | Use context-based shutdown; proper goroutine synchronization |\n521: | Port conflicts | Low | Medium | Configurable ports; check port availability; clear error messages |\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ## Verification\n526: \n527: ### Build Verification\n528: \n529: ```bash\n530: # Build all binaries\n531: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n532: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n533: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n534: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n535: \n536: # Verify binaries exist\n537: ls -la bin/\n538: ```\n539: \n540: ### Help Verification\n541: \n542: ```bash\n543: # Each binary should print help\n544: ./bin/agentd --help\n545: ./bin/router --help\n546: ./bin/workload-manager --help\n547: ./bin/picod --help\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Startup Verification (Local)\n551: \n552: ```bash\n553: # Test picod (no external deps)\n554: ./bin/picod --port=18080 &\n555: sleep 1\n556: curl http://localhost:18080/health || echo \"Health check not implemented yet\"\n557: kill %1\n558: \n559: # Test agentd (requires K8s config, will fail gracefully)\n560: ./bin/agentd --kubeconfig=/dev/null 2>&1 | head -5\n561: \n562: # Test with missing required flags\n563: ./bin/router 2>&1 | grep -q \"required\" && echo \"Flag validation works\"\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ### Graceful Shutdown Test\n567: \n568: ```bash\n569: # Test graceful shutdown\n570: timeout 2 ./bin/picod --port=18081 &\n571: sleep 0.5\n572: kill -TERM %1\n573: wait %1\n574: echo \"Exit code: $?\"  # Should be 0\n575: ```\n576: \n577: ### Docker Build Verification\n578: \n579: ```bash\n580: # Build container images\n581: make docker-build\n582: \n583: # Verify images\n584: docker images | grep agentcube\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - [AR-019 Delta Spec](changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md) — Detailed requirements\n592: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n593: - [Deployment Design](deployment/design.md) — Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n594: - [CLI Toolkit Design](cli-toolkit/design.md) — Python CLI design\n595: - [project.md](project.md) — Project context and architecture\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## Success Criteria\n600: \n601: 1. ✅ All 4 binaries compile without errors\n602: 2. ✅ Each binary prints help with `--help` flag\n603: 3. ✅ Each binary validates required flags and exits with error if missing\n604: 4. ✅ agentd starts controller-runtime manager with Sandbox reconciler\n605: 5. ✅ router starts Gin HTTP server and connects to Redis\n606: 6. ✅ workload-manager starts controller and HTTP API server\n607: 7. ✅ picod starts HTTP server and initializes workspace\n608: 8. ✅ All binaries handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n609: 9. ✅ Exit codes are correct (0 for success, non-zero for errors)\n610: 10. ✅ Docker builds succeed for all binaries\n611: 11. ✅ Binaries log startup messages with version and configuration\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: *AR-019 — Module: cmd — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 615 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **agentd** — Idle cleanup controller binary that runs the Sandbox reconciler\n2. **router** — HTTP session routing proxy with Gin framework\n3. **workload-manager** — Sandbox orchestration controller with Kubernetes CRD management","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775882167613,"end":1775882167630}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882167635,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad35c90001Fyl1stmRPRjwsx","messageID":"msg_d7ad330500018776jvXIJe555O","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n2: \n3: go 1.23.0\n4: \n5: require (\n6: \tgithub.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.37.0\n7: \tgithub.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1\n8: \tgithub.com/google/go-cmp v0.7.0\n9: \tgithub.com/google/uuid v1.6.0\n10: \tgithub.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.19.1\n11: \tgithub.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.7.3\n12: \tgithub.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.56\n13: \tgolang.org/x/net v0.37.0\n14: \tk8s.io/api v0.32.0\n15: \tk8s.io/apimachinery v0.32.0\n16: \tk8s.io/client-go v0.32.0\n17: \tk8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n18: \tsigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.0\n19: )\n20: \n21: require (\n22: \tgithub.com/beorn7/perks v1.0.1 // indirect\n23: \tgithub.com/cespare/xxhash/v2 v2.3.0 // indirect\n24: \tgithub.com/davecgh/go-spew v1.1.2-0.20180830191138-d8f796af33cc // indirect\n25: \tgithub.com/dgryski/go-rendezvous v0.0.0-20200823014737-9f7001d12a5f // indirect\n26: \tgithub.com/emicklei/go-restful/v3 v3.11.0 // indirect\n27: \tgithub.com/evanphx/json-patch/v5 v5.9.0 // indirect\n28: \tgithub.com/fsnotify/fsnotify v1.7.0 // indirect\n29: \tgithub.com/fxamacker/cbor/v2 v2.7.0 // indirect\n30: \tgithub.com/go-logr/logr v1.4.2 // indirect\n31: \tgithub.com/go-openapi/jsonpointer v0.21.0 // indirect\n32: \tgithub.com/go-openapi/jsonreference v0.20.2 // indirect\n33: \tgithub.com/go-openapi/swag v0.23.0 // indirect\n34: \tgithub.com/gogo/protobuf v1.3.2 // indirect\n35: \tgithub.com/golang/protobuf v1.5.4 // indirect\n36: \tgithub.com/google/gnostic-models v0.6.8 // indirect\n37: \tgithub.com/google/gofuzz v1.2.0 // indirect\n38: \tgithub.com/josharian/intern v1.0.0 // indirect\n39: \tgithub.com/json-iterator/go v1.1.12 // indirect\n40: \tgithub.com/mailru/easyjson v0.7.7 // indirect\n41: \tgithub.com/modern-go/concurrent v0.0.0-20180306012644-bacd9c7ef1dd // indirect\n42: \tgithub.com/modern-go/reflect2 v1.0.2 // indirect\n43: \tgithub.com/munnerz/goautoneg v0.0.0-20191010083416-a7dc8b61c822 // indirect\n44: \tgithub.com/pkg/errors v0.9.1 // indirect\n45: \tgithub.com/prometheus/client_model v0.6.1 // indirect\n46: \tgithub.com/prometheus/common v0.55.0 // indirect\n47: \tgithub.com/prometheus/procfs v0.15.1 // indirect\n48: \tgithub.com/spf13/pflag v1.0.5 // indirect\n49: \tgithub.com/x448/float16 v0.8.4 // indirect\n50: \tgithub.com/yuin/gopher-lua v1.1.1 // indirect\n51: \tgolang.org/x/exp v0.0.0-20230515195305-f3d0a9c9a5cc // indirect\n52: \tgolang.org/x/oauth2 v0.23.0 // indirect\n53: \tgolang.org/x/sys v0.31.0 // indirect\n54: \tgolang.org/x/term v0.30.0 // indirect\n55: \tgolang.org/x/text v0.23.0 // indirect\n56: \tgolang.org/x/time v0.7.0 // indirect\n57: \tgomodules.xyz/jsonpatch/v2 v2.4.0 // indirect\n58: \tgoogle.golang.org/protobuf v1.35.1 // indirect\n59: \tgopkg.in/evanphx/json-patch.v4 v4.12.0 // indirect\n60: \tgopkg.in/inf.v0 v0.9.1 // indirect\n61: \tgopkg.in/yaml.v3 v3.0.1 // indirect\n62: \tk8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver v0.31.0 // indirect\n63: \tk8s.io/kube-openapi v0.0.0-20241105132330-32ad38e42d3f // indirect\n64: \tk8s.io/utils v0.0.0-20241104100929-3ea5e8cea738 // indirect\n65: \tsigs.k8s.io/json v0.0.0-20241010143419-9aa6b5e7a4b3 // indirect\n66: \tsigs.k8s.io/structured-merge-diff/v4 v4.4.2 // indirect\n67: \tsigs.k8s.io/yaml v1.4.0 // indirect\n68: )\n\n(End of file - total 68 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n\ngo 1.23.0\n\nrequire (\n\tgithub.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.37.0\n\tgithub.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1\n\tgithub.com/google/go-cmp v0.7.0\n\tgithub.com/google/uuid v1.6.0\n\tgithub.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.19.1\n\tgithub.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.7.3\n\tgithub.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.56\n\tgolang.org/x/net v0.37.0\n\tk8s.io/api v0.32.0\n\tk8s.io/apimachinery v0.32.0\n\tk8s.io/client-go v0.32.0\n\tk8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n\tsigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.0\n)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod","time":{"start":1775882167615,"end":1775882167633}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882167647,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad34ad7001RjHMww7xHHqhCN","messageID":"msg_d7ad330500018776jvXIJe555O","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-019\n6: **Module:** `cmd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** M\n9: **Base Spec:** project.md, deployment/design.md\n10: \n11: AR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components: `agentd` (idle cleanup controller), `router` (session routing), `workload-manager` (sandbox orchestration), and `picod` (sandbox daemon). Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, and start the respective service with graceful shutdown handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Binary Entry Point Structure\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide 4 binary entry points under `cmd/`: `cmd/agentd/main.go`, `cmd/router/main.go`, `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, and `cmd/picod/main.go`. Each SHALL use standard Go flag parsing with sensible defaults and support graceful shutdown via OS signal handling.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Binary compiles successfully\n22: - **GIVEN** the `cmd/` directory contains the 4 binary entry point files\n23: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd/... && go build ./cmd/router/... && go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && go build ./cmd/picod/...` is executed\n24: - **THEN** all 4 binaries SHALL compile without errors\n25: - **AND** the output binaries SHALL be runnable with `--help` flag\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Binary prints help\n28: - **GIVEN** any of the 4 binaries is built\n29: - **WHEN** the binary is executed with `--help` flag\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL print usage information including available flags\n31: - **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Agentd Binary Entry Point\n36: \n37: The `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL parse flags for Kubernetes configuration, construct a controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1`, disable metrics and health probe servers, and run the idle cleanup reconciler.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Agentd starts with default flags\n40: - **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n41: - **AND** flags include `--kubeconfig` (optional, default: in-cluster), `--sync-period` (default: 5m)\n42: - **WHEN** the binary starts without arguments in a cluster environment\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL construct manager with in-cluster config\n44: - **AND** it SHALL start the reconciler with 5-minute sync period\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Agentd handles graceful shutdown\n47: - **GIVEN** agentd is running\n48: - **WHEN** SIGINT or SIGTERM is received\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL gracefully stop the manager\n50: - **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### Requirement: Router Binary Entry Point\n55: \n56: The `cmd/router/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, debug mode, Redis/Valkey connection, session store configuration, and backend workload manager endpoint. It SHALL construct a Gin HTTP server with session routing middleware.\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router starts with default flags\n59: - **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n60: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--debug` (default: false), `--redis-addr` (required), `--workload-manager` (required)\n61: - **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL construct Gin router with session middleware\n63: - **AND** it SHALL listen on the specified port\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Router validates required flags\n66: - **GIVEN** router binary is built\n67: - **WHEN** started without required flags (`--redis-addr` or `--workload-manager`)\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL print error message indicating missing flags\n69: - **AND** it SHALL exit with non-zero code\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Binary Entry Point\n74: \n75: The `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, Kubernetes config, Redis/Valkey connection, image defaults, and sandbox defaults. It SHALL construct the workload manager with controller and HTTP API server.\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Workload manager starts with default flags\n78: - **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n79: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--kubeconfig` (optional), `--redis-addr` (required), `--default-image` (default: \"ubuntu:22.04\")\n80: - **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL construct the workload manager controller\n82: - **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP API server on the specified port\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ### Requirement: Picod Binary Entry Point\n87: \n88: The `cmd/picod/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port and workspace root. It SHALL construct the picod server with code execution, file upload/download, and exec streaming capabilities.\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Picod starts with default flags\n91: - **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n92: - **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--workspace` (default: current directory)\n93: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL resolve workspace to absolute path\n95: - **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP server with code execution handlers\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Picod validates workspace\n98: - **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n99: - **WHEN** started with `--workspace=/nonexistent/path`\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL attempt to create the directory\n101: - **AND** if creation fails, it SHALL log fatal error and exit\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## Interface\n106: \n107: ### Binary: agentd\n108: \n109: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n110: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n111: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n112: | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Period for full sync of all sandboxes |\n113: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n114: \n115: ### Binary: router\n116: \n117: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n118: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n119: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n120: | `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug mode with request logging |\n121: | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n122: | `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | Workload manager endpoint URL (required) |\n123: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n124: \n125: ### Binary: workload-manager\n126: \n127: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n128: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n129: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n130: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n131: | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n132: | `--default-image` | string | \"ubuntu:22.04\" | Default sandbox image |\n133: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace for sandboxes |\n134: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n135: \n136: ### Binary: picod\n137: \n138: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n139: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n140: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n141: | `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n142: | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Behavior\n147: \n148: ### Common Behavior\n149: \n150: All 4 binaries SHALL:\n151: 1. Parse flags using Go's `flag` package\n152: 2. Log startup message with version and flag values (except secrets)\n153: 3. Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n154: 4. Return exit code 0 on clean shutdown, non-zero on fatal errors\n155: 5. Support `--help` to print usage and exit cleanly\n156: \n157: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n158: \n159: ```\n160: 1. Receive SIGINT/SIGTERM\n161: 2. Log \"Shutting down gracefully...\"\n162: 3. Create context with timeout (graceful-timeout)\n163: 4. Call server/manager Shutdown() with timeout context\n164: 5. Wait for shutdown or timeout\n165: 6. If timeout exceeded, log warning and force exit\n166: 7. Exit with code 0 (or 1 if timeout exceeded)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Dependencies\n172: \n173: | Package | Purpose |\n174: |---------|---------|\n175: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Agentd manager construction |\n176: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | Kubernetes config loading |\n177: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Router HTTP framework |\n178: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n179: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n180: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/*` | Internal packages |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Testing\n185: \n186: ### Scenario: All binaries compile\n187: ```bash\n188: go build ./cmd/agentd/... && \\\n189: go build ./cmd/router/... && \\\n190: go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && \\\n191: go build ./cmd/picod/...\n192: ```\n193: **Expected:** All commands succeed with no output (or warnings only).\n194: \n195: ### Scenario: All binaries print help\n196: ```bash\n197: ./agentd --help\n198: ./router --help\n199: ./workload-manager --help\n200: ./picod --help\n201: ```\n202: **Expected:** Each prints flag usage and exits with code 0.\n203: \n204: ### Scenario: Graceful shutdown test\n205: ```bash\n206: timeout 2 ./agentd --sync-period=1s &\n207: sleep 0.5\n208: kill %1\n209: wait %1\n210: echo \"Exit code: $?\"\n211: ```\n212: **Expected:** Exit code is 0 after graceful shutdown message.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## Deliverables\n217: \n218: | Path | Description |\n219: |------|-------------|\n220: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agentd binary entry point |\n221: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Router binary entry point |\n222: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Workload manager binary entry point |\n223: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Picod binary entry point |\n224: \n\n(End of file - total 224 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-019\n**Module:** `cmd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n**Base Spec:** project.md, deployment/design.md\n\nAR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components: `agentd` (idle cleanup controller), `router` (session routing), `workload-manager` (sandbox orchestration), and `picod` (sandbox daemon). Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, and start the respective service with graceful shutdown handling.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Binary Entry Point Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide 4 binary entry points under `cmd/`: `cmd/agentd/main.go`, `cmd/router/main.go`, `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, and `cmd/picod/main.go`. Each SHALL use standard Go flag parsing with sensible defaults and support graceful shutdown via OS signal handling.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882167609,"end":1775882167644}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775882167667,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad3655f001bsB55zeipgnAGi","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ad330500018776jvXIJe555O","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22117,"input":4,"output":267,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":4490,"read":17356}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882173127,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad37ac6001ar1E24AhyeB5om","messageID":"msg_d7ad3658c0011wBNQ0dlskUnha","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882179074,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad38d87001wIdDeu0E0uxXDl","messageID":"msg_d7ad3658c0011wBNQ0dlskUnha","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: \n10: Provide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Valid token allows request\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token in the Authorization header\n22: - **WHEN** a request is made to a PicoD execution endpoint\n23: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL validate the token and allow the request to proceed\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Missing token returns 401\n26: - **GIVEN** a request without an Authorization header\n27: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Invalid token format returns 401\n31: - **GIVEN** a request with an Authorization header not starting with \"Bearer \"\n32: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n33: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid authorization format\"}`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n36: - **GIVEN** a request with an expired JWT token\n37: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Malformed token returns 401\n41: - **GIVEN** a request with a malformed JWT token\n42: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token malformed\"}`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n46: - **GIVEN** a request with a JWT token signed with wrong key\n47: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token signature invalid\"}`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Token Claims Extraction and Context Propagation\n53: \n54: The system SHALL extract JWT claims and store them in the request context for downstream handlers.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Claims stored in context\n57: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id claim\n58: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n59: - **THEN** the extracted claims SHALL be stored in the request context\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Session ID extracted from token\n62: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n63: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n64: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve session_id from context\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: User ID extracted from token\n67: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with user_id=\"user-456\"\n68: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n69: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve user_id from context\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Sandbox ID extracted from token\n72: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with sandbox_id=\"sandbox-789\"\n73: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n74: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve sandbox_id from context\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Namespace extracted from token\n77: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with namespace=\"default\"\n78: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n79: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve namespace from context\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Multiple claims extracted\n82: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace, and runtime_kind claims\n83: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n84: - **THEN** all claims SHALL be available in the context for downstream use\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Session ID Validation Middleware\n89: \n90: The system SHALL verify that the session_id claim is present and valid.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing session_id returns 403\n93: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token without a session_id claim\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id claim is required\"}`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Empty session_id returns 403\n98: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with empty session_id=\"\"\n99: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id cannot be empty\"}`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Session ID matches request parameter\n103: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/abc123\n104: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n105: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Session ID mismatch returns 403\n108: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/def456\n109: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session access denied\"}`\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Optional Authentication Support\n115: \n116: The system SHALL support optional authentication for specific endpoints.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Optional auth allows anonymous requests\n119: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n120: - **WHEN** a request without a token is made\n121: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed without claims in context\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Optional auth extracts claims when present\n124: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n125: - **WHEN** a request with a valid token is made\n126: - **THEN** the claims SHALL be extracted and stored in context\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Optional auth ignores invalid tokens\n129: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n130: - **WHEN** a request with an invalid token is made\n131: - **THEN** the request SHALL proceed without claims (invalid token is treated as no token)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: JWT Configuration\n136: \n137: The system SHALL support configurable JWT settings for the PicoD middleware.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Configuration from environment variables\n140: - **GIVEN** environment variables `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER`, `PICOD_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`, and `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY`\n141: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is initialized\n142: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL be populated from these environment variables\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Configuration with public key PEM\n145: - **GIVEN** a valid RSA public key in PEM format in configuration\n146: - **WHEN** the middleware validates tokens\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL use the configured public key to verify signatures\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Configuration with JWKS endpoint\n150: - **GIVEN** a JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint URL in configuration\n151: - **WHEN** the middleware needs to validate tokens\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL fetch the public key from the JWKS endpoint\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Invalid configuration returns error\n155: - **GIVEN** an invalid JWT configuration (e.g., empty issuer)\n156: - **WHEN** the middleware is initialized\n157: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n160: - **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n161: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is loaded\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL use sensible defaults (issuer=\"picod\", expiry=5m)\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Token Refresh Support\n167: \n168: The system SHALL support token refresh for extended sessions.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Refresh token endpoint\n171: - **GIVEN** a valid refresh token\n172: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token\n173: - **THEN** the server SHALL return a new access token and refresh token pair\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Expired refresh token returns 401\n176: - **GIVEN** an expired refresh token\n177: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n178: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"refresh token expired\"}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Invalid refresh token returns 401\n181: - **GIVEN** an invalid refresh token\n182: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n183: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid refresh token\"}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Public Key Endpoint\n188: \n189: The system SHALL expose a public key endpoint for token verification by clients.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Get public key\n192: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with RSA keys\n193: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/.well-known/jwks.json`\n194: - **THEN** the server SHALL return the public key in JWKS format\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Public key includes key ID\n197: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with key versioning\n198: - **WHEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n199: - **THEN** the response SHALL include the key ID (kid) for each key\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Public key algorithm specified\n202: - **GIVEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n203: - **WHEN** the response is returned\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL include the algorithm (alg: RS256) and key type (kty: RSA)\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n209: \n210: The system SHALL expose metrics for JWT middleware operations.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Token validation counter\n213: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n214: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validations_total` counter with labels for result (success/failure)\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Token validation latency\n218: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n219: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` histogram\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Active session tracking\n223: - **GIVEN** tokens are being validated\n224: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_active_sessions` gauge with session_id labels\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Logging\n230: \n231: The system SHALL implement structured logging for JWT middleware operations.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Successful authentication logged\n234: - **GIVEN** a request with valid token is processed\n235: - **WHEN** authentication succeeds\n236: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, user_id, endpoint, duration\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Failed authentication logged\n239: - **GIVEN** a request with invalid token is processed\n240: - **WHEN** authentication fails\n241: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: error, error_code, endpoint, remote_addr\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token refresh logged\n244: - **GIVEN** a token refresh request is processed\n245: - **WHEN** refresh succeeds or fails\n246: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, result, duration\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n251: \n252: The system SHALL provide consistent error responses for authentication failures.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: WWW-Authenticate header on 401\n255: - **GIVEN** an unauthenticated request\n256: - **WHEN** the middleware returns HTTP 401\n257: - **THEN** the response SHALL include `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer` header\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JSON error response format\n260: - **GIVEN** an authentication error occurs\n261: - **WHEN** the error response is sent\n262: - **THEN** it SHALL be JSON with fields: error, message, code (optional)\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Error code classification\n265: - **GIVEN** various authentication failures\n266: - **WHEN** errors are returned\n267: - **THEN** each SHALL have a machine-readable code: TOKEN_EXPIRED, TOKEN_INVALID, TOKEN_MALFORMED, MISSING_CLAIMS\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## File Index\n272: \n273: | Path | Purpose |\n274: |------|---------|\n275: | `pkg/picod/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT authentication middleware implementation |\n276: | `pkg/picod/jwt_config.go` | JWT configuration structures and loading |\n277: | `pkg/picod/jwt_types.go` | JWT types and context keys for PicoD |\n278: | `pkg/picod/jwt_handlers.go` | HTTP handlers for auth endpoints (refresh, JWKS) |\n279: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | JWT and authentication error definitions |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Dependencies\n284: \n285: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n286: |------------|---------|---------|\n287: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token parsing and validation |\n288: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Local | Shared JWT types and utilities |\n289: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n290: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics collection |\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## API Endpoints\n295: \n296: | Method | Path | Auth Required | Description |\n297: |--------|------|---------------|-------------|\n298: | POST | `/execute/{session_id}` | Yes | Execute command in sandbox |\n299: | GET | `/execute/{id}/status` | Yes | Get execution status |\n300: | GET | `/execute/{id}/output` | Yes | Stream execution output |\n301: | DELETE | `/execute/{id}` | Yes | Cancel execution |\n302: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | No | Refresh access token |\n303: | GET | `/.well-known/jwks.json` | No | Get public keys in JWKS format |\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Integration Points\n308: \n309: | Component | Integration |\n310: |-----------|-------------|\n311: | `pkg/router` | Reuses JWTManager for token validation; imports TokenClaims type |\n312: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | Reads session_id from context to validate execution requests |\n313: | `pkg/store` | May store refresh token metadata for revocation |\n314: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Coordinates JWT configuration across components |\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Notes\n319: \n320: - The PicoD JWT middleware leverages the existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation where possible\n321: - Token claims must include `session_id` for all PicoD execution endpoints\n322: - The middleware supports both mandatory and optional authentication patterns\n323: - Public keys are exposed via JWKS endpoint for external verification\n324: - Metrics are prefixed with `picod_` to distinguish from router metrics\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nProvide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid token allows request","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882179061,"end":1775882179071}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882179081,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad3885b0013fcfJwn6THjxvh","messageID":"msg_d7ad3658c0011wBNQ0dlskUnha","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018\n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** S\n9: **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n18: \n19: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n22: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n23: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n24: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the change\n25: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked with the object's namespace and name\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n28: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n29: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n30: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the deletion\n31: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked to handle cleanup\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Input\n36: \n37: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n40: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists without the `last-activity-time` annotation\n41: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n42: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n43: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Empty annotation value means no deletion\n46: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists with `last-activity-time` annotation set to empty string\n47: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n48: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n49: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Parsing\n54: \n55: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp parses successfully\n58: - **GIVEN** annotation value is a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n59: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` is called\n60: - **THEN** the timestamp SHALL be parsed successfully\n61: - **AND** reconciliation SHALL proceed to expiration check\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues with error\n64: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"invalid-time\")\n65: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n66: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n67: - **AND** the error SHALL be logged\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Malformed timestamp requeues\n70: - **GIVEN** annotation value is malformed (e.g., \"2024-13-45T99:99:99Z\")\n71: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n72: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Expiration Threshold\n77: \n78: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n81: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n82: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n83: - **AND** `time.Now()` is after `expirationTime`\n84: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n85: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n86: - **AND** on success, reconcile SHALL return empty result with nil error\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n89: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n90: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n91: - **AND** `time.Now()` is before `expirationTime`\n92: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n93: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n94: - **AND** no delete SHALL occur\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Exactly at expiration triggers delete\n97: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is exactly 15 minutes ago\n98: - **AND** `time.Now()` equals `expirationTime`\n99: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n100: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Delete Idempotency\n105: \n106: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox handled gracefully\n109: - **GIVEN** the API server returns `NotFound` on delete\n110: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n111: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n112: - **AND** no error SHALL be logged\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Delete conflict returns error for retry\n115: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a conflict error on delete\n116: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n117: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n118: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Delete network error returns error for retry\n121: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on delete\n122: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n123: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n124: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Get Not Found Handling\n129: \n130: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n133: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists when Get is called\n134: - **AND** the API server returns `NotFound`\n135: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n136: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: Manager Configuration\n141: \n142: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Manager starts with correct configuration\n145: - **GIVEN** the scheme contains core Kubernetes types\n146: - **AND** the scheme contains `sandboxv1alpha1` types\n147: - **AND** metrics server is disabled\n148: - **AND** health probe server is disabled\n149: - **WHEN** the manager is created\n150: - **THEN** the manager SHALL start without error\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n153: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n154: - **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n155: - **THEN** the manager SHALL stop gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Changes to Base Specification\n160: \n161: This AR implements the Agentd idle cleanup controller using the client-go library interfaces defined in deployment/client-go.md. No modifications to existing interfaces.\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## New Interfaces\n166: \n167: ### Reconciler Interface\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: package agentd\n171: \n172: import (\n173:     \"context\"\n174:     \"time\"\n175: \n176:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n177:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n178:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller/controllerutil\"\n179:     ctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n180: )\n181: \n182: // SessionExpirationTimeout defines the idle timeout before sandbox deletion\n183: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n184: \n185: // Reconciler reconciles Sandbox objects for idle cleanup\n186: type Reconciler struct {\n187:     client.Client\n188:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n189: }\n190: \n191: // Reconcile implements the idle cleanup logic\n192: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n193: \n194: // SetupWithManager sets up the controller with the Manager\n195: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### Main Entry Point\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // cmd/agentd/main.go\n202: \n203: // Scheme registration\n204: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()\n205: \n206: func init() {\n207:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n208:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n209: }\n210: \n211: // main creates and runs the controller-runtime manager\n212: func main()\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## Modified Interfaces\n218: \n219: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Behavioral Changes\n224: \n225: | Behavior | Before | After |\n226: |----------|--------|-------|\n227: | Sandbox lifecycle | No automatic cleanup | Automatic deletion after 15 min idle |\n228: | Resource tracking | No activity tracking | last-activity-time annotation read |\n229: | Reconciliation | N/A | Controller-runtime reconciler watches Sandboxes |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n236: |------------|---------|---------|\n237: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.x | Controller-runtime framework |\n238: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Local | Sandbox CRD types |\n239: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.x | Kubernetes API errors |\n240: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | v0.x | Kubernetes runtime types |\n241: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Local | Annotation key constants |\n242: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client (base spec) |\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## File Index\n247: \n248: | Path | Purpose |\n249: |------|---------|\n250: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation with idle cleanup logic |\n251: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler |\n252: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entry point and manager setup |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## Constants\n257: \n258: | Constant | Value | Description |\n259: |----------|-------|-------------|\n260: | `SessionExpirationTimeout` | `15 * time.Minute` | Idle timeout before sandbox deletion |\n261: | `RequeueAfterParseError` | `30 * time.Second` | Requeue delay when timestamp parse fails |\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ## Configuration\n266: \n267: ### Environment Variables\n268: \n269: None. The controller uses hardcoded constants for configuration.\n270: \n271: ### Annotations Read\n272: \n273: | Annotation Key | Source | Description |\n274: |---------------|--------|-------------|\n275: | `last-activity-time` | `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` | RFC3339 timestamp of last sandbox activity |\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## API Endpoints Summary\n280: \n281: This AR is a controller (reconciler) that watches Kubernetes resources; no new API endpoints are exposed.\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Watched Resources\n286: \n287: | API Group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n288: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n289: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Create, Update, Delete |\n290: \n291: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Migration Notes\n296: \n297: - Ensure `sandboxv1alpha1` scheme is registered before starting the manager\n298: - The workload manager must set `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandboxes for cleanup to function\n299: - Existing Sandboxes without the annotation will not be cleaned up\n300: - Deploy agentd binary alongside other agentcube components\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n305: \n306: 1. **Reconciliation**: Controller-runtime reconciler registered for Sandbox resources\n307: 2. **Annotation Reading**: Correctly reads `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n308: 3. **Timestamp Parsing**: Parses RFC3339 timestamps; handles parse errors with 30s requeue\n309: 4. **Expiration Logic**: Correctly computes expiration time (lastActivity + 15 minutes)\n310: 5. **Idle Detection**: Deletes sandboxes idle for more than 15 minutes\n311: 6. **Future Requeue**: Requeues with appropriate delay when expiration is in the future\n312: 7. **Idempotency**: Handles NotFound errors gracefully (no error returned)\n313: 8. **Error Handling**: Returns errors for retry on transient failures\n314: 9. **Manager Setup**: Correctly configures controller-runtime manager with scheme\n315: 10. **Signal Handling**: Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n316: 11. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on reconciler logic\n\n(End of file - total 316 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n**Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882179055,"end":1775882179077}}}}
