{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882292812,"sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad43e6100129XEX8tj6NYo9p","messageID":"msg_d7ad39237001KkP4Vbx8l67vWQ","sessionID":"ses_2852d14c5ffemqmGQLLUOKGbvL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry (4 binaries) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-019\n**Module:** `cmd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n**Base Spec:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\nAR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components: `agentd` (idle cleanup controller), `router` (session routing), `workload-manager` (sandbox orchestration), and `picod` (sandbox daemon). Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, and start the respective service with graceful shutdown handling.\n\nThe base spec defines the client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` with `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Binary Entry Point Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide 4 binary entry points under `cmd/`: `cmd/agentd/main.go`, `cmd/router/main.go`, `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, and `cmd/picod/main.go`. Each SHALL use standard Go flag parsing with sensible defaults and support graceful shutdown via OS signal handling.\n\n#### Scenario: Binary compiles successfully\n- **GIVEN** the `cmd/` directory contains the 4 binary entry point files\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd/... && go build ./cmd/router/... && go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && go build ./cmd/picod/...` is executed\n- **THEN** all 4 binaries SHALL compile without errors\n- **AND** the output binaries SHALL be runnable with `--help` flag\n\n#### Scenario: Binary prints help\n- **GIVEN** any of the 4 binaries is built\n- **WHEN** the binary is executed with `--help` flag\n- **THEN** it SHALL print usage information including available flags\n- **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Agentd Binary Entry Point\n\nThe `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL parse flags for Kubernetes configuration, construct a controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `runtimev1alpha1` (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), disable metrics and health probe servers, and run the idle cleanup reconciler.\n\n#### Scenario: Agentd starts with default flags\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n- **AND** flags include `--kubeconfig` (optional, default: in-cluster), `--sync-period` (default: 5m)\n- **WHEN** the binary starts without arguments in a cluster environment\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct manager with in-cluster config\n- **AND** it SHALL register the reconciler for `AgentRuntime` resources\n- **AND** it SHALL start the reconciler with 5-minute sync period\n\n#### Scenario: Agentd handles graceful shutdown\n- **GIVEN** agentd is running with controller-runtime manager\n- **WHEN** SIGINT or SIGTERM is received\n- **THEN** it SHALL gracefully stop the manager\n- **AND** it SHALL exit with code 0\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router Binary Entry Point\n\nThe `cmd/router/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, debug mode, Redis/Valkey connection, session store configuration, and backend workload manager endpoint. It SHALL construct a Gin HTTP server with session routing middleware.\n\n#### Scenario: Router starts with default flags\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n- **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--debug` (default: false), `--redis-addr` (required), `--workload-manager` (required)\n- **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct Gin router with session middleware\n- **AND** it SHALL listen on the specified port\n\n#### Scenario: Router validates required flags\n- **GIVEN** router binary is built\n- **WHEN** started without required flags (`--redis-addr` or `--workload-manager`)\n- **THEN** it SHALL print error message indicating missing flags\n- **AND** it SHALL exit with non-zero code\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Binary Entry Point\n\nThe `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port, Kubernetes config, Redis/Valkey connection, and resource defaults. It SHALL construct the workload manager with controller for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs and HTTP API server.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload manager starts with default flags\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n- **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--kubeconfig` (optional), `--redis-addr` (required)\n- **WHEN** the binary starts with required flags provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct the workload manager controller for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` types\n- **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP API server on the specified port\n\n#### Scenario: Workload manager registers CRD schemes\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` initializes the controller-runtime manager\n- **WHEN** the scheme is being configured\n- **THEN** it SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types from `runtimev1alpha1`\n- **AND** it SHALL use REST resource plurals `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` as defined in base spec\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Picod Binary Entry Point\n\nThe `cmd/picod/main.go` SHALL parse flags for HTTP port and workspace root. It SHALL construct the picod server with code execution, file upload/download, and exec streaming capabilities.\n\n#### Scenario: Picod starts with default flags\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go` exists with flag parsing\n- **AND** flags include `--port` (default: 8080), `--workspace` (default: current directory)\n- **WHEN** the binary starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL resolve workspace to absolute path\n- **AND** it SHALL start the HTTP server with code execution handlers\n\n#### Scenario: Picod validates workspace\n- **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n- **WHEN** started with `--workspace=/nonexistent/path`\n- **THEN** it SHALL attempt to create the directory\n- **AND** if creation fails, it SHALL log fatal error and exit\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### Binary: agentd\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n| `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Period for full sync of all AgentRuntimes |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n\n### Binary: router\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug mode with request logging |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n| `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | Workload manager endpoint URL (required) |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n\n### Binary: workload-manager\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig file (empty for in-cluster) |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | Redis/Valkey server address (required) |\n| `--default-namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace for AgentRuntimes |\n| `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n\n### Binary: picod\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n| `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n\n---\n\n## Behavior\n\n### Common Behavior\n\nAll 4 binaries SHALL:\n1. Parse flags using Go's `flag` package\n2. Log startup message with version and flag values (except secrets)\n3. Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n4. Return exit code 0 on clean shutdown, non-zero on fatal errors\n5. Support `--help` to print usage and exit cleanly\n\n### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n\n```\n1. Receive SIGINT/SIGTERM\n2. Log \"Shutting down gracefully...\"\n3. Create context with timeout (graceful-timeout)\n4. Call server/manager Shutdown() with timeout context\n5. Wait for shutdown or timeout\n6. If timeout exceeded, log warning and force exit\n7. Exit with code 0 (or 1 if timeout exceeded)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nThis AR consumes the client-go library defined in `deployment/client-go.md`. The following types from the base spec are used:\n\n| Type | Package | Usage |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` | `client-go` | Resource reconciled by workload-manager |\n| `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` | `client-go` | Resource reconciled by workload-manager |\n| `versioned.Interface` | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | Kubernetes client interface |\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` | `client-go/typed/runtime/v1alpha1` | Typed client for runtime group |\n\nNo modifications to the base client-go interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Agentd/workload-manager manager construction |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | Kubernetes config loading |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Router HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Base spec: generated Kubernetes client |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agentd binary entry point |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Router binary entry point |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Workload manager binary entry point |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Picod binary entry point |\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n### Scenario: All binaries compile\n```bash\ngo build ./cmd/agentd/... && \\\ngo build ./cmd/router/... && \\\ngo build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && \\\ngo build ./cmd/picod/...\n```\n**Expected:** All commands succeed with no output (or warnings only).\n\n### Scenario: All binaries print help\n```bash\n./agentd --help\n./router --help\n./workload-manager --help\n./picod --help\n```\n**Expected:** Each prints flag usage and exits with code 0.\n\n### Scenario: Graceful shutdown test\n```bash\ntimeout 2 ./agentd --sync-period=1s &\nsleep 0.5\nkill %1\nwait %1\necho \"Exit code: $?\"\n```\n**Expected:** Exit code is 0 after graceful shutdown message.\n\n### Scenario: Workload manager scheme registration\n```bash\n# Verify workload-manager can initialize with CRD scheme\n./workload-manager --redis-addr=localhost:6379 --kubeconfig=/dev/null 2>&1 | head -5\n```\n**Expected:** Error should relate to connection, not scheme registration.\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Agentd binary entry point with AgentRuntime reconciler |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Router binary entry point with Gin and session routing |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Workload manager with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter controller |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Picod binary entry point with workspace handling |\n\n---\n\n*AR-019 — Module: cmd — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882292795,"end":1775882292810}}}}
